HEADWORD: Deutoplasm
<hw>Deu"to*plasm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>deuto-</ets> + Gr. <grk>pla`sma</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The lifeless food matter in the cytoplasm of an
ovum or a cell, as distinguished from the active or true protoplasm;
yolk substance; yolk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deutoplastic</ent>⟦br⟧
